<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Attempting the following does not work as I would expect:</p>

<p>$oForm-&gt;addElement(
            'text',
            'section,
            array(
                'label'      =&gt; 'Bound Inserts CPT:',
                'validators' =&gt; array(
                    array(
                        new Zend_Validate_Float(),
                        'breakChainOnFailure' =&gt; true
                    ).
                    new Another_Validator()
                ),
                'filters'    =&gt; array('StringTrim'),
                'allowEmpty' =&gt; true
            )
        );</p>

<p>Seen:
'Value is required and can't be empty'</p>

<p>Expected:
The validation message from the Float validator.</p>

<p>I realise the documentation states (in its round about way ) that this is what happens but I'd like to have the option instead of having to provide an array of messages for use by the NotEmpty validator.</p>

